  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      One of the major problems of systemic sclerosis (SSc) patients is suggested to be articular
      involvement. Mostly involved joints in SSc were reported as wrist,
      carpometacarpal-interphalangeal, foot, knee, hip and shoulder however there have been little
      knowledge on sacroiliac joint. Here the investigators plan a study on the involvement of
      this joint in SSc.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
